Retired Supreme Court Justice John Paul Stevens has passed away, and President Trump and First Lady Melania Trump offer their condolences to his family and friends. Justice Stevens, a decorated World War II Naval Officer, was known for his humility, legal expertise, and love for the Chicago Cubs. His work during his 35 years on the Supreme Court will continue to influence the legal framework of the United States in the future. His passion for the law and for the country will be remembered.